       Commands whose behavior depends on the  type  of  terminal
       should  accept  arguments of the form -Tterm where term is
       one of the names given above; if no such argument is  pre-
       sent,  such  commands should obtain the terminal type from
       the environment variable TERM, which, in turn, should con-
       tain term.

